The paper deals with a graph problem related to dominating sets and metric dimension, which are classic topics in discrete mathematics and graph theory. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The problem also involves the complexity of the problem on trees and bipartite subcubic graphs, which suggests categories such as cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper uses approximation algorithms and parameterized complexity, which are topics commonly found in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
